description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Staff &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Vacancies: Clinical Team Leader – Anaesthetics Trauma&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating Department Practitioners, Anaesthetic Nurses &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are working to develop an expanded service for the Dorset community and wider areas. Poole is a great place to live and work where patient care and staff welfare are our top priorities. We are located in Poole town centre near the coast and New Forest. you will have the flexibility of working across both Poole and Bournemouth Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At this exciting time, are you what we are looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the management team in place and focus on quality, transformation and service development, we are increasing our operating theatre suite and are looking for motiavted people, to join our expanding theatre department delivering a 24 hour service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer great opportunities with an extensive educational program, to include the development of Surgical First Assistants (SFA), Assistant Theatre practitioners, nurse associates, leadership and management development to name but a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on our friendly working environment and our desire to lead on Best Practice in the Operating Theatre setting. If you have the knowledge, skills, experience and drive that we are looking for to join our friendly and supportive team, then theatres is the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with multi professional colleagues, you will have post qualification experience, working in an operating theatre setting across different specialities – with your core team being in the Anaesthetics for Trauma. other areas within the theatre department are, gynaecology, Recovery, obstetrics, general surgery, anaesthetics and head and neck– and you will become a valued member of the team. We encourage duel or multi skilled practitioners, however full training will be given to facilitate development. and there is a requirement that you ay be needed to cross site work. Your peers, Anaesthetists, surgeons and senior staff will support you to learn new skills and to expand your practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Operating Department Practitioner or Anaesthetic Nurse with the recognised qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have post qualification experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: week commencing 23/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INFORMAL VISITS ARE MOST WELCOME AND ENCOURAGED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange a visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jenny Miller, Clinical Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jennifer.miller@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
